cs.DB, cs.LO, cs.AI, cs.DS, cs.CC

This paper deals with the semantics of incomplete databases, which is a topic closely related to databases and logic. Therefore, cs.DB (Databases) and cs.LO (Logic in Computer Science) are the most likely sub-categories. The paper also discusses algorithms and complexity, which suggests that it could also belong to cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) and cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms). Finally, the paper mentions homomorphic covers, which are a concept from category theory, indicating a possible connection to cs.CC (Computational Complexity).
